column4: When I boot from my Live USB, it says it can't find a medium with a live file system
Where are you at on this?
I am on WIndows 7 if that's what you mean
I mean I saw you working on this earlier. Have you got any closer. What have you tried?
i've remade it with both unetbootin and universal usb installer, it didn't work
What error do you get when starting?
it says "Cannot find a medium with a live file system" then it switches to BusyBox. BTW, I've tried this on my other laptop, it works.
The same usb stick iso works on another laptop?
correct
are you there?
I believe this error means that you are getting to the kernel but there is a problem with the kernel going forward. What iso are you using?
lubuntu-11.04.iso
Have you tried any other iso?
what others are there?
maybe 10.10?
ok i'll try, also check private message
would it matter if i had extra files on my live usb
no it should not matter Should be looking for iso
ok, now should i extract the iso files onto the usb or just put the actual iso file
Do you have access to a llinux distro to create the bootable usb. Also have you tried pulling the stickout out and reinserting when you get to the error?
no and no
